Description

Abstract base class representing a book in the library system.

The Borrowable interface defines a contract for any resource that can be borrowed.

Class to represent borrowing records for books.
EBook
Represents an electronic book in the library system.

Abstract class representing a general electronic resource in the library.
Faculty
Represents a faculty in the university system.
FacultyRules
Represents rules specific to a faculty for managing resources like books, meeting rooms, and electronic resources.

Represents a library in the university system.

MeetingRoom
Represents a meeting room in a library that can be reserved by users.

Represents a PC as a type of electronic resource in the library.
Person
The abstract base class representing a person in the library system.

The PhysicalBorrowableBook class represents a physical book in the library system that can be borrowed and reserved by users.

Represents a physical book that cannot be borrowed.
Professor
Represents a professor in the library system.
Reservable
Interface for resources that can be reserved.
Student
Represents a student in the university's library system.
Tablet
Represents a Tablet as a type of electronic resource in the library.It inherits from ElectronicResource.
University
Represents a university containing multiple faculties and their libraries.
User
Abstract class representing a general user in the library system, such as a student or professor.
